                <h3>Terms of Use and Privacy</h3>
                <p>By using this website, app and/or tool (collectively the "Tool") or by providing your personal information, you agree that your personal information can be used for the purpose of Canadian immigration, citizenship or temporary residence assessment as well as for communication of professional service offerings that may be of value to you for Canadian immigration, citizenship or temporary residence qualifications or status.</p>
                <p>The content provided is for informational and contact purposes only. No professional relationship of advice or representation is hereby offered or created. Users are encouraged to use the information provided to further explore immigration topics and, where appropriate and when desired, to use the services of qualified professionals before acting on any information provided. </p>
                <p>While we strive to update the Tool regularly, changes to immigration rules, requirements and guidelines or your personal circumstances may make the information out of date or incomplete.   Any statements or information made through the Tool are not guaranteed and are subject to verification as well as ultimate eligibility decisions by the applicable Canadian immigration officials. </p>
                <p>We may make changes to the content from time to time.  We may also make changes to the terms of use and privacy provisions.  Changes to the terms of use and privacy provisions will not be applied retroactively.</p>
                <p>Communication and contact features of the Tool and the internet may not be secure, and confidentiality and security cannot be guaranteed when information is transmitted by email or other electronic communication. </p>
                <p>We recognize the importance of privacy and the sensitivity of personal information received by us. All personal information received by us is stored and protected in accordance with Canadian privacy laws.</p>
                <p>We may use cookies to improve performance and to determine trends.</p>
                <p>The Tool and all content and intellectual property associated with it, including data and stored data, are the property of Our Canada Services Inc. </p>
                <p>You agree not to reproduce, copy, sell, resell or exploit for any commercial purpose, any portion of the Tool or its content or data other than as expressly authorized by Our Canada Services Inc. in writing. </p>
                <p>You agree that you will not damage, disable, overburden, or impair the Tool or interfere with any person's use and enjoyment of it.</p>
                <p>Copyright © 2020 , Trademark TM, Patent Pending, Our Canada Services Inc.   All rights reserved.  The Tool is protected by Canadian and international intellectual property laws. Except for your use as authorized above, you may not modify, reproduce or distribute the Tool, or individual sections of the content, design or layout or any other component of the Tool without express prior written permission.</p>
                <p>By agreeing to these terms, you acknowledge that the Tool and its owner may collect, use and disclose your information as described herein.</p>
                <p>Our Canada Services Inc. is a “Data Controller” when it processes personal data related to and/or received from its users and ultimately takes responsibility for managing that data in compliance with applicable data privacy regulations. Consequently, any obligation to enter into a “personal data processing agreement” does not apply and such agreements shall not be signed.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>You may contact us through the Contact us page of the Tool. </li>
                    <li> Data collection and usage</li>
                    <li>We will collect the following personal data:</li>
                    <li>Contact information: your name, position, role, company or organisation, telephone (including mobile phone number where provided) as well as email and postal address and residence;</li>
                    <li>Personal and family information;</li>
                    <li>Education history information;</li>
                    <li>Work history information;</li>
                    <li>Job offer information;</li>
                    <li>Business information: data identifying you in relation to matters on which you instruct us or in which you are involved;</li>
                    <li>Your profile name, login ID and password for access to the Tool;</li>
                    <li>Subscriptions/preferences / requests for professional assistance: when you ask to receive updates or newsletters as well as consent preferences to help us identify which materials you are interested in receiving;</li>
                    <li>Events data: attendance at and provision of feedback forms in relation to our events;</li>
                    <li>Supplier data: contact details and other information about you or your company or organisation where you provide services to the Tool or its users;</li>
                    <li>Technical information: when you access this website and our technology services being IP address, browser type and version (e.g. Internet Explorer, Firefox, Safari etc.), time zone setting, browser plug-in types and versions, operating system you are using (e.g. Vista, Windows XP, MacOS, etc.), device type, hardware model, MAC address, unique identifiers and mobile network information;</li>
                    <li>Online data: when you access this website and our technology services, information about your visit including URL clickstream to, through and from our website (including date and time), information about your network as such as information about devices, nodes, configurations, connection speeds and network application performance; pages viewed or searched for, page response times, download errors, length of visits and interaction information (such as scrolling, clicks, mouse-overs) and whether you click on particular links or open our emails. </li>
                </ul>
                <br>
                <p>We do not collect personal data about your online activities across third party websites or online services.</p>
                <p>Criminal record data: where appropriate, such as information about prior criminal offences (or confirmation of clean criminal record).</p>
                <p>The above data will be provided to us by you, your family member or other person is a user or professional user and who is using the Tool. </p>
                <ul>
                    <li> We may also collect information that you choose to provide in communications with us. </li>
                    <li>How we use your personal data</li>
                    <li>We use your personal data for the following purposes:</li>
                    <li>To analyse your eligibility for Canadian immigration, citizenship, temporary residence and related programs;</li>
                    <li>To respond to your request for service provisions;</li>
                    <li>Managing and administering your account and communication and to target our marketing and communication with you;</li>
                    <li>Communication: sending emails, newsletters and other messages to keep you informed of immigration developments, market insights and of service offerings;</li>
                    <li>Events;</li>
                    <li>Surveys and feedback: including events feedback as well as answering issues and concerns which may arise;</li>
                    <li>Website monitoring: to check the website and our other technology services are being used appropriately and to optimise their functionality;</li>
                    <li>Online security: protecting our information assets and technology platforms from unauthorised access or usage and to monitor for malware and other security threats;</li>
                    <li>Regulatory: compliance with legal and regulatory obligations;</li>
                    <li>Managing suppliers: who deliver services to us;</li>
                    <li>Managing service providers: who may deliver services to you;</li>
                    <li>Legitimate interest: to pursue the legitimate business interests listed in the “Legitimate Interests” section of this policy below.</li>
                </ul>
                <br>
                <p>Our reasons for using your personal data.  We will process your personal data for reasons, including:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>you have given us consent: for example where you share details for particular purposes;</li>
                    <li>processing is necessary for our legitimate business interests or those of a third party:  provided this does not override any interests or rights that you have as an individual. Our legitimate interests are listed in the next section.</li>
                </ul>
                <p><b>Legitimate interests</b></p>
                <p>We have legitimate business interests in:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>responding to requests by users for professional services and other services and referring those requests to service providers;</li>
                    <li>sharing data with service providers in order to respond to requests by users;</li>
                    <li>managing our business and relationship with you and service providers;</li>
                    <li>understanding and responding to inquiries and client feedback;</li>
                    <li>understanding how our users use our services and websites;</li>
                    <li>identifying what our clients want and developing our relationship with you or your family;</li>
                    <li>improving our services and offerings; </li>
                    <li>receiving information from service providers for users;</li>
                    <li>enforcing our terms of engagement and website and other terms and conditions;</li>
                    <li>ensuring our systems are secure;</li>
                    <li>managing our supply chain;</li>
                    <li>developing relationships with service providers;</li>
                    <li>ensuring debts are paid;</li>
                    <li>operating suppressors to exclude you from direct marketing if you unsubscribe; </li>
                    <li>sharing data in connection with acquisitions and transfers of our business. </li>
                </ul>
                <p>Our reasons for using special category data</p>
                <p>Special category data in the EU and certain other jurisdictions refers to sensitive data such as your health data and criminal convictions. We will process this data where:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>we have your explicit consent: for the particular processing; </li>
                    <li>this is necessary to conduct assessments for immigration programs; </li>
                    <li>this is necessary to deal with requests for services and is relevant to your potential admissibility; </li>
                    <li>this is necessary for substantial public interest: for example to prevent or detect unlawful acts; </li>
                    <li>as permitted by applicable law: outside the EU and other jurisdictions where these restrictions apply.</li>
                </ul>
                <p><b>With whom do we share your data?</b></p>
                <p>We share your information with others as follows:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>With service providers, when you have requested assistance:  including service provider's management, staff and contractors in order to respond to your request for services;</li>
                    <li>Suppliers: who support our Tool including IT and communication suppliers, outsourced business support, marketing and advertising agencies and back up. Our suppliers have to meet minimum standards as to information security and they will only be provided data in line with their function;</li>
                    <li>Shared service centres: operated by us or third parties, including for on-boarding, IT services, marketing, risk management and office support services;</li>
                    <li>Appropriate parties in the event of emergencies: in particular to protect health and safety of our clients, staff and organisations;</li>
                    <li>You or your family: in relation to us responding to your requests and for communication;</li>
                    <li>Screening service providers: so that we can comply with legal obligations and other required checks;</li>
                    <li>Advertising networks and analytics service providers: to support and display ads on our website, apps and other social media tools;</li>
                    <li>Third parties: in the context of the acquisition or transfer of any part of our business or in connection with the business reorganisation;</li>
                    <li>Other delegates: where your name will appear on the attendee list for events where you have told us you plan to attend.</li>
                </ul>
                <p><b>Personal data about others</b></p>
                <p>In some cases, you may provide personal data to us about other people (such as your family members, employers, prospective employers or clients). You must ensure that you have given those individuals an appropriate notice that you are providing their information to us and have obtained their consent to that disclosure. </p>
                <p><b>Security</b></p>
                <p>We will hold your information securely in line with physical, technical and administrative security measures. However, the transmission of information via the internet is not completely secure. Although we will take reasonable measures to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee the security of your information transmitted and any transmission is at your own risk. </p>
                <p><b>Where will your information be held? </b></p>
                <p>We are based in Canada and our users and service providers are around the world.  Your information may be transferred out of your local jurisdiction or region. Data protection laws vary by country and those applicable in the USA and elsewhere are not equivalent to those applicable in, for example, the EU or certain other jurisdictions.  If you would like copies of the standard contractual clauses applicable to European data, please contact us.</p>
                <p><b>How long do we keep your data?</b></p>
                <p>We generally keep your information as needed to communicate service offerings and to comply with our requirements.  This will depend on factors such as whether you request services or continue to communicate with us or subscribe for information or attend events.  We will retain your information as necessary to comply with legal, accounting or service requirements. Typical retention periods will range from 3 to 14 years. </p>
                <p><b>Your Rights</b></p>
                <p>You have certain rights in relation to your information.</p>
                <p>If you would like to exercise, or discuss, any of these rights, please contact us as outlined below or through the Contact Us part of the Tool. </p>
                <p>Access: you are entitled to ask us if we are processing your data and, if we are, you can request access to your personal data.  This enables you to receive a copy of the personal data we hold about you and certain other information about it;</p>
                <p>Correction: you are entitled to request that any incomplete or inaccurate personal data we hold about you is corrected; </p>
                <p>Erasure: you are entitled to ask us to delete or remove personal data in certain circumstances. There are also certain exceptions where we may refuse a request for erasure, for example, where the personal data is required for compliance with law or previous agreements; </p>
                <p>Restriction: you are entitled to ask us to suspend the processing of certain of your personal data about you, for example if you want us to establish its accuracy or the reason for processing it; </p>
                <p>Transfer: you may ask us to help you request the transfer certain of your personal data to another party; </p>
                <p>Objection: where we are processing your personal data based on a legitimate interest (or those of a third party) and you may challenge this.  However, we may be entitled to continue processing your information. You also have the right to object where we are processing your personal information for direct marketing purposes;</p>
                <p>Automated decisions: you may contest any automated decision made about you where this has a legal or similar significant effect and ask for it to be reconsidered.  However, please note that we make no immigration related decisions.  All immigration related decisions are made by Canadian governments and their officials and not by anyone affiliated with the Tool. </p>
                <p>Consent: where we are processing personal data with consent, you can withdraw your consent.</p>
                <p>If you want to exercise any of these rights, please contact us as outlined below or through the contact us section of the Tool. </p>
                <p>You also have a right to lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority, in particular in the Member State in the European Union where you are habitually resident where we are based or where an alleged infringement of Data Protection law has taken place. In the UK you can make a complaint to the Information Commissioner's Office (Tel: 0303 123 1113 or at www.ico.org.uk) . </p>
                <p><b>Right to object</b></p>
                <p>You may have a right to object to us processing your information in certain circumstances. This applies where we are processing your personal information based on a legitimate interest (or those of a third party) you may challenge this.  However, we may be entitled to continue processing your information based on our legitimate interests or where this is relevant to claims.  You also have the right to object where we are processing your personal information for direct marketing purposes. </p>
                <p><b>Direct Marketing </b></p>
                <p>You can opt-out of receiving direct marketing from us at any time.</p>
                <p>We may use the information you give us on our website or other means for direct marketing purposes to provide emails, newsletters and other messages to keep you informed of immigration developments, market insights and of our services including events that we think may interest you. </p>
                <p>You can opt-out of receiving direct marketing from us at any time.  You can do this by changing your account settings, by clicking on the "unsubscribe" link included at the end of any marketing email we send to you, or by contacting us.</p>
                <p><b>Cookies</b></p>
                <p>We may use cookies that identify your browser. They collect and store information when you visit our website about how you use it through which it is possible to record your use of the website, as well as provide you with a better service and experience when browsing and for analytics. The personal data we collect through these technologies will also be used to manage your session.</p>
                <p><b>Links or responses by service providers</b></p>
                <p>You may, from time to time, be contacted by service providers or connected with service providers.  The personal data that you provide them is not our responsibility.  If you have any concerns relating to same, please contact the service provider directly. </p>
                <p>If you connect to another website, that website may have its privacy notices which may set out how your information is collected and processed when visiting that site. </p>
                <p>We do not knowingly collect information from children or other persons who are under 16 years old. If you are under 16 years old, you may not submit any personal data to us. </p>
                <p><b>How to contact us </b></p>
                <p>If you would like more information about the way we manage personal data that we hold about you or if you have concerns about the use of your data, please contact <a href="mailto:info@ourcanada.co ">info @ ourcanada.co </a> </p>
                <p>This notice and the terms of use may be changed from time to time.  Changes will not be retroactive. </p>
